%S A397066 1,1,1,2,3,2,4,5,5,6,6,9,10,11,10,12,17,17,20,22,19,25,27,32,36,45,34,
%T A397066 46,44,49,58,70,73,77,80,86,84,97,103,125,139,145,146,176,153,173,175,
%U A397066 206,218,266,260,293,318,310,319,343,339,384,420,458,512,558,577
%N A397066 Number of partitions of n whose parts admit exactly one superdiagonal arrangement, that is, exactly one ordering (c_1,...,c_k) with c_i >= i.
%C A397066 The unique arrangement is necessarily the weakly increasing one, so a counted partition is in particular superdiagonal (its i-th smallest part is at least i).
%C A397066 Structure (with proof): write the distinct values as v_1 < ... < v_t with multiplicities m_1,...,m_t and cumulative counts C_s = m_1 + ... + m_s. The partition is counted if and only if v_s = C_s for all s < t and v_t >= C_t = k, the number of parts. Thus every non-maximal value equals the number of parts not exceeding it, and the partition is determined by its multiplicity vector together with its largest part.
%C A397066 The subsequence of counted partitions with all parts equal is A038548(n), the number of divisors of n not exceeding sqrt(n); this divisor layer makes the sequence non-monotone, e.g., a(5) = 2 < 3 = a(4) and a(26) = 34 < 45 = a(25).
%C A397066 Summing the number of superdiagonal arrangements over all partitions of n gives A219282. The partitions attaining the maximal number k!/(m_1!...m_t!) of arrangements are the partitions counted by A003114, by the first Rogers-Ramanujan identity.
%H A397066 Mohammad F. Marashdeh, <a href="/A397066/b397066.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A397066 G.f.: 1 + Sum_{t>=1} Sum_{m_1,...,m_t >= 1} x^(C_1*m_1 + C_2*m_2 + ... + C_t*m_t) / (1 - x^(m_t)), where C_s = m_1 + ... + m_s.
%e A397066 a(9) = 6: the partitions of 9 with a unique superdiagonal arrangement are [9], [1,8], [1,2,6], [1,4,4], [2,2,5], and [3,3,3].
%o A397066 (Python)
%o A397066 from functools import lru_cache
%o A397066 @lru_cache(None)
%o A397066 def g(C, rem):
%o A397066     tot, m = 0, 1
%o A397066     while m*(C + m) <= rem:
%o A397066         if rem % m == 0 and rem//m >= C + m: tot += 1
%o A397066         r2 = rem - (C + m)*m
%o A397066         if r2 >= C + m + 1: tot += g(C + m, r2)
%o A397066         m += 1
%o A397066     return tot
%o A397066 def a(n): return 1 if n == 0 else g(0, n)
%o A397066 print([a(n) for n in range(63)])
%Y A397066 Cf. A219282, A098131, A003114, A038548, A236310.
%K A397066 nonn,new
%O A397066 0,4
